public class Node
extends org.antlr.runtime.tree.CommonTree

The Class Node. This subclass of CommonTree is used to check for the contextual constrains of the Noot language. Furthermore it is used to annotate the AST with important information such as type information and if the Node yields a return value.

shouldIgnoreReturnValue

public boolean shouldIgnoreReturnValue()
Should ignore return value. This method will be used in the code generator to check if this node yields a return value.

Returns:
true, if the return value of this node should be ignored

setIgnoreReturnValue

public void setIgnoreReturnValue(boolean ignoreReturnValue)
Sets the ignore return value. Set this value to true if the node should not yield a return value the default behavior is that it does. This will be propagated through all the ValuePropagatingChildren. This important for code generation.

Parameters:
ignoreReturnValue - the new ignore return value

addValuePropagatingChild

public void addValuePropagatingChild(Node ValuePropagatingChild)
Adds the value propagating child. If setIgnoreReturnValue() is called on this Node it will be propagated through all the ValuePropagatingChildren. This is needed to support value returning in nested CompoundExpressions for example.

Parameters:
ValuePropagatingChild - the value propagating child

addValuePropagatingChildren

public void addValuePropagatingChildren(List<Node> list)
Adds the value propagating children. If setIgnoreReturnValue() is called on this Node it will be propagated through all the ValuePropagatingChildren. This is needed to support value returning in nested CompoundExpressions for example.

Parameters:
list - the list
